The paper discusses constrained optimization in the context of machine learning, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Bayesian optimization and game theory also suggests potential relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Game Theory). The paper also mentions non-differentiable and discontinuous constraints, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
